From: Peter Kokot <peterkokot@gmail.com>
Subject: Add CMake changes for PHP-8.3 branch

* EditorConfig adjustments for code style support in editors and IDEs;
* Minimal CMake build system generated files added to root '.gitignore'
  file and 'ext/skeleton/.gitignore.in' (for out-of-source builds only,
  PHP CMake-based system is configured to disable the in-source builds);
* CMake adjustments added to run-tests.php for info about failing tests
  and checks;
* CMake-related modifications added to 'ext/skeleton' template directory
  and 'ext/ext_skel.php' script;
* Added 'TEST_PHP_FPM_EXECUTABLE' environment variable to sapi/fpm to
  enable setting the location of the php-fpm executable in case it
  isn't available in usual locations. For example, in case of the CMake
  multi-config generators, such as Ninja Multi-Config
  ('sapi/fpm/Debug/php-fpm', 'sapi/fpm/Release/php-fpm', etc.).
* Adjusted code comments.
* Added some basic documentation related to CMake-based build system.
* Added PHP CMake package config file and PHP CMake modules to Autotools
  installation for building PHP extensions with CMake when PHP is built
  and installed on the host with Autotools.
